Skogres are skeletal ogres who have invaded the dance site of Jiggig, south of Castle Wars. They have continued the dance that they did there in life during undeath and show no signs of stopping. They are encountered during the Zogre Flesh Eaters quest. Their name appears to be a portmanteau of "skeleton" and "ogre". They count as both skeletons and ogres for Slayer tasks, and the one playing the drums by the entrance even counts as a zombie.

An aggressive Skogre also has a chance to spawn next to the player when burying Zogre bones inside Jiggig.

Strengths and weaknesses[edit | edit source]

Skogres take heavily reduced damage from normal weapons (approximately 75% reduction). Like Zogres, they are especially weak to Brutal arrows, taking full damage. They also take full damage from poison and familiars.

Update history[edit | edit source]

This information has been compiled as part of the update history project. Some updates may not be included – see here for how to help out!
  • patch 17 April 2023 (Update):
    • Fixed the issue of incorrect souls being captured by Ushabti.
  • patch 11 April 2023 (Update):
    • Can be killed as part of the new undead slayer task.
  • patch 10 August 2020 (Update):
    • It is no longer possible to spawn extra skogres when burying zogre bones in an area with multiple zogres.
  • patch 7 March 2016 (Update):
    • Skogres have had their combat stats rebalanced.
  • update 17 May 2005 (Update):
    • Added to game.

Trivia[edit | edit source]

  • The examine text for all skogres was "It's falling apart!" before a graphical update. Some skogres retain this examine text.
